es, but that seems unlikely. Instead, I could consider using direct reflection to set SimpleLog.class$org$... to Thread.class. But then again, I’m wondering if that would actually change Class.getClassLoader. It looks like it might not. I need to clarify my approach here to make sure I’m heading in the right direction.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_bSViOJRUCLAC5adcaycPJPIj|fc_0518d4fd267024b20169f4f2d3443481a0b8e9769b8c7bdfc0", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.apache.htrace/htrace-core/3.1.0-incubating/build.gradle", "limit": 180}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1243, "output": 1727, "cacheRead": 38912, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 41882, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777660602565, "responseId": "resp_0518d4fd267024b20169f4f2bb07e881a083f9ce1641e683d2"}}
